# Prefer Native Built-ins

- Prefer native platform features (e.g. `Object.groupBy`, `Object.entries`, `Object.fromEntries`, `Array.prototype.map/filter/reduce/flatMap/find/toSorted`, `Map`, `Set`, `URL`, `Intl`) when they are supported by this project's target runtimes.
- Prefer native `Object.*` and `Array.*`/`Array.prototype.*` utilities over manual loops for transformations, grouping, filtering, sorting, and lookups.
- Do not re-implement standard library behavior unless there is a demonstrated compatibility, performance, or readability reason.
- If compatibility is uncertain, verify project targets first and then choose native by default.
- During review/refactor, simplify custom utility code to native equivalents when behavior stays the same.

## Examples

```ts
// Avoid manual grouping loops when native groupBy is available.
const grouped = Object.groupBy(items, (item) => item.type ?? 'Autre');

// Use immutable native sorting for derived views.
const sorted = items.toSorted((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
```
